  <h1>Privacy Policy — Fixation</h1>
  <p class="updated"><em>Last updated: July 5, 2026</em></p>

  <h2>Who We Are</h2>
  <p>Fixation is published by Kerri Williams. If you have questions about this policy, contact us at tmrw.pod@gmail.com.</p>

  <h2>What We Collect and Why</h2>
  <p><strong>Reading lists and preferences.</strong> When you use Fixation, you can save series to your personal reading list (Want to Read, Currently Reading, Completed, Dropped, On Hold), rate titles, and filter by trope preferences. This data is stored to power your personal library and recommendations, and is associated with your account so it persists across sessions.</p>
  <p><strong>Community content.</strong> If you post discussion comments, create community lists, or otherwise contribute content visible to other users, that content is stored and may be visible to other Fixation users. Do not include personal information in anything you post publicly, since community content is, by nature, seen by other members.</p>
  <p><strong>Device identifier / account identifier.</strong> We generate and store an identifier tied to your account to associate your reading lists, preferences, and any community content with you. This identifier is not linked to your real name or contact information unless you choose to provide that information yourself (for example, in a username or profile bio).</p>
  <p><strong>Subscription status.</strong> We use RevenueCat to manage subscriptions. RevenueCat receives your app store account's anonymous subscriber ID to verify your subscription status. We do not receive or store your payment details — those are handled entirely by Apple or Google. RevenueCat's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy">revenuecat.com/privacy</a>.</p>
  <p><strong>Usage data.</strong> We may collect basic usage data (such as which features are used and how often) to understand how Fixation is used and to improve the app.</p>

  <h2>What We Do Not Collect</h2>
  <p>We do not host or distribute copyrighted manga or manhwa content ourselves. Fixation links out to third-party, officially licensed platforms for reading — we do not collect data about what you read on those external platforms. We do not sell your data to anyone, ever. We do not use your data for third-party advertising.</p>

  <h2>Third Parties</h2>
  <p>We share data with the following third parties, limited to what is necessary to operate the service:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RevenueCat</strong> — subscription management (anonymous subscriber ID and purchase status)</li>
    <li><strong>Our hosting provider</strong> — your account data (reading lists, preferences, community content) is stored on secure servers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We link out to third-party officially licensed reading platforms (such as Webtoon, Lezhin, Tappytoon, Manta, and similar services) as part of Fixation's core recommendation feature. Once you leave Fixation to read on one of these platforms, their own privacy policy governs your data, not this one. We encourage you to review the privacy policy of any external platform you use.</p>

  <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <p>Your account data is stored on secure servers. We use industry-standard encryption for data in transit and at rest.</p>

  <h2>Your Rights and Controls</h2>
  <p>You can export your data or delete your account and all associated data at any time from within the app's Settings. Deletion is permanent and complete. If you are located in the EU, UK, or California, you have additional rights under GDPR and CCPA respectively, including the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data. Contact us at tmrw.pod@gmail.com to exercise any of these rights.</p>

  <h2>Community Content and Moderation</h2>
  <p>Content you post in community features (discussion, lists, comments) may be visible to other users of Fixation. We reserve the right to remove content that violates our Terms of Use. If you believe another user's content violates our terms or your rights, contact us at tmrw.pod@gmail.com.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>Fixation is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>If we make material changes to how we collect or use data, we will update this page and change the "last updated" date at the top. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

